description:
The God of Thunder heads West, recast in some of cinema's most iconic roles! Marvel's THOR GOES HOLLYWOOD variants, honoring the Odinson's feature-film debut, are now collected under one cover!


Collection of various variant covers from 2011 Marvel comics, each featuring Thor or members of Thor's supporting cast in scenes that were homages to famous Hollywood movies, all as promotion for the release of Thor's eponymous film.

The covers collected in this one-shot, and the respective homages are:

A) Amazing Spider-Man #658 by Paul Renaud --- cover depicts Sif battling the Brood, in a homage to the Alien movies

B) Avengers Academy #13 by Amanda Conner --- cover depicts Thor, Sif, Enchantress and the Warriors Three dancing, in a homage to The Breakfast Club

C) Black Panther: The Man Without Fear #517 by John Tyler Christopher --- cover depicts Loki sitting on a park bench, in a homage to Forrest Gump

D) Captain America #617 by Khoi Pham --- cover depicts Thor and Odin with a glass wall between them, in a homage to The Silence of the Lambs

E) FF #2 by Greg Horn --- cover depicts Thor battling Loki, in a homage to The Matrix

F) Generation Hope #7 by Gabriel Hardman --- cover depicts the cast of Thor replicating the poster of Inception

G) Heroes for Hire #5 by Greg Horn --- cover depicts Thor charging at a shark, in a homage to Jaws

H) Incredible Hulks #627 by Mike del Mundo --- cover depicts Thor and Sif replicating the "I'm flying, Jack!" scene from Titanic

I) Invincible Iron Man #503 by Sebastian Fiumara --- cover depicts Loki replicating the "Heeeere's Johnny!" scene from The Shining

J) Iron Man 2.0 #4 by Sebastian Fiumara --- cover depicts Kid Loki in a recreation of The Social Network's poster

K) Journey into Mystery #622 by Lee Weeks --- cover depicts Thor discovering the Cask of Ancient Winters in a homage to Raiders of the Lost Ark

L) New Avengers #11 by Amanda Conner --- cover depicts Thor and Enchantress in a homage to The Graduate

M) Secret Avengers #12 by Michael Kaluta --- cover depicts Thor in a homage to Modern Times

N) Uncanny X-Force #7 by Mike del Mundo --- cover depicts Thor in a homage to Frankenstein

O) Uncanny X-Men #535 by Humberto Ramos --- cover depicts Thor, Loki and the Warriors Three in a homage to The Usual Suspects

P) Wolverine #8 by Dale Keown --- cover depicts Thor in a homage to Rocky

Q) Wolverine: The Best There Is #5 by Simone Bianchi --- cover depicts Thor and the Destroyer in a homage to The Terminator

R) X-23 #9 by Chris Stevens --- cover depicts Thor in a homage to King Kong

S) X-Men #10 by John Tyler Christopher --- cover depicts Sif and Volstagg in a homage to Saturday Night Fever

T) X-Men Legacy #247 by Khoi Pham --- cover depicts Thor in a homage to Planet of the Apes
name: Thor Goes Hollywood

description: Decisions are made that cannot be reversed as the friends set out on their paths, to world destruction or salvation, only time will tell. The dramatic conclusion to the first chapter of THE BUNKER.
name: The Man In the Photograph

From the famed tales of 1001 Nights, Keeping Up With The Jinns features two genies that go to battle trying to resolve a conflict dating back over 2,000 years!
name: Keeping Up With the Jinns

description:
Let the mayhem begin! PJ takes center stage in the arena, determined to be crowned king of the underground hi-tech battle royale. It's man-made machine vs. man-made machine and more! In the streets of Paris, Malikai and Sonia learn more about the growing movement known as Gabriel's Voice, and their strong belief in magic--despite ever seeing any firsthand-something Malikai could change with the snap of his finger. Also, as Grace and Vanyss enjoy a common bond, other magical people are being hunted down half a world away in San Francisco - but by whom and for what purpose?

List of covers and their creators:

name: Ladies Night

description:
For Every ACTION....there is a REACTION! The adventures of our heroes ACTION CAT and ADVENTURE BUG continue! What happens when Evil Cat zaps a hero with his mysterious new EVIL-RAY-5000? You may expect a certain unexpected REACTION! WHOAH! Watch out! ALSO! What is this? SOUTHPAW is has a plot to take over the world? Aw, say it ain't so! Time to call the President...then order a pizza! ALSO! Pie is served for dessert in a very unique style! The people of beautiful downtown Skokie are in for a treat! Last but not least...The Jaywalker Strikes! Created by Art Baltazar & Franco, the same guys who brought you TINY TITANS, SUPERMAN FAMILY ADVENTURES, and itty bitty HELLBOY! True story!

Story Titles

  • Equal & Opposite!
  • The Ring of Ultimate Evil!
  • Pizza Conference!
  • Never Bring A Ray Gun To A Pie Fight!
  • Meet the Jaywalker!
  • Equal & Opposite part 2!
  • Zombie Cat Visits His Insurance Agent!
The Butler did it. Or more precisely, the butler's cousin. See what happens when Alfred's identical, criminal relative captures Batman's loyal servant and tries to take his place in Wayne Manor.
name: Zelda's Great Escape!

description: Amber and Zavi break into the lab to grow The Endling a body, but their pursuers are closing in.

Now that Brianna's on the train to Mommy-ville, her sisters are determined to curb some of her less maternal habits. All trips to the plasma rifle range, antimatter cannon ammo experiments, and high-G aero-mech joy rides are out until the baby's born! It's a strange case of "taming of the shrew" as Britanny tries to take Brianna from grenade pins and gunpowder to safety pins and talcum powder!

Note: The digital edition (12/24/2013) for this issue was released before the print edition (1/22/2014).

In issue 4 of HAWKEN: MELEE, a family farm is torn apart by the fallout of corporate warfare, and a mother does everything she can to provide for her family the best way she knows how: by joining the fight. Writer Andrew E.C. Gaska (Space: 1999, Critical Millennium) and artist Dan Dussault (Critical Millennium, Robotech) bring you "Lapse", a harrowing tale of ashes and effort to the world of HAWKEN.
name: Lapse

description: It's the end of the world! The unstable robot Udarnik is transforming all ore on the Moon into the liquid metal Phlogistone - a process that will create enough of the cosmic poison to kill everyone on Earth, assuming it doesn't tear the Moon apart first. With Tony Stark literally dying on his feet, trying to pilot someone else's armor and unable to tell reality from hallucination, can he save Earth from a toxic future?

Vincent Price is the master of the cult gothic horror films. In this graphic novel is the sequels to the classic films Witchfinder General, Last Man on Earth and Tingler.

Story Titles

  • Witchfinder
  • Tinglers Part 1
  • Tinglers Part 2
  • Last Man
name: Volume 10

description:
Who Ya Gonna Call?

As the world is pushed into another war, the witch hunters are called to the aid of two great nations. Hunters Xing and Tarras head east to the Bairong Empire, close on the heels of a man who shares Xing's face. But what is Xing's connection to the Empire? Meanwhile, Tasha Godspell is sent south to Camelot, on a quest that will bring him one step closer to his bewitching sister, Aria. But first, he'll need to survive a perilous road trip...

Chapter Titles

  • Chapter 17: The Nonexistent Witch
  • Chapter 18: Sun, Moon, And Star
  • Chapter 19: Assassination
  • Chapter 20: To Become A King
name: Vol. 5

description: Louise and her spellcasting companions have been sent on a top secret mission to the Kingdom of Albion, where the royal family is besieged on all sides by rebelling nobles. They are accompanied by the dashing Viscount Wardes, who is not only captain of the Griffin Crops but is also Louise's longtime fianc√©. Saito can't help but feel jealous of the impressive captain, but there's a more pressing concern: will they find the Prince of Albion in time before the kingdom is lost?
name: Vol. 5

character_credits.name: Louise Francoise Le Blanc de La Valliere

first_appearance_characters.name: Louise Francoise Le Blanc de La Valliere

description: This is it: the big finale! All the worlds and heroes of Moon Lake come together to defend planet Earth from the incoming alien threat!

LeAnn Heywood is the world's current Seeker, a 'superhero' if you will assigned to a special task force whose goal is to take on criminals, corrupt corporations, and terrorists cells where ever they may be. But there is a former Seeker, Tracy LeMaster who is locked up in a mental hospital because obviously, her story of being an incarnate of an ancient Atlantean force that enhabits the Seeker host body couldn‚Äôt possibly be true. But as LeAnn carries out her duties as Seeker, a new recuit, Maxine Brasura, is unknowingly in training to become a Seeker herself. Seeker. Some say she is an assassin, some claim her as a hero. She is a figure of mystery that seemingly moves within the shadows to exact her vengeance. She is also an operative for a special government task force unit and the Seeker persona has come out of the shadows to become a popular icon for the American public. A woman who wears the mantle of Seeker proudly for she understands that she is Seeker and Seeker is her. But she's wrong. Before her there was another Seeker...and before that...yet another...and another. There has always been a Seeker. They may look different. They may "serve" different masters...but the role of Seeker goes beyond current day government, goes beyond operatives against other operatives. The legacy of Seeker goes into the fabled past of a land that most don't believe exists.

person_credits.name: Charles M. Schulz
person_credits.role: writer, penciler, letterer, inker, colorist, cover

description: Gihren uses Garma's funeral to rally support and energize the people of Zeon. Ranba Ral, the commander of the Zanzibar class battleship, enters Earth's atmosphere to go up against the White Base. Not content to sit in his chair, Ranba Ral goes out to fight the Gundam in his Mobile Suit, triggering a battle of cataclysmic proportions.

A young cadet named Dragas has only ever known war. He was enlisted in the Ruteni faction at a young age and battles the Kadaal faction in an everlasting war for control of the war-torn planet. Just as it seems Dragas has met his last moments, a man swooping down on a technologically advanced spaceship saves him and offers him a job opportunity as a space-charting alien-fighting mercenary! This is the adventure of Dragas, the Pathfinder!

Sam Spade meets Dawn of the Dead!

Set in a post-apocalyptic near future, DeadTown follows the exploits of CHAN who, having lost his family in the zombie plague, works as a private detective in a world crawling with the undead.

Visually inspired by the rich black and white style of films like Touch of Evil and The Maltese Falcon, DeadTown combines the finest film noir traditions with the zombie horror genre, in an edgy re-imagining of the hard boiled detective thriller. Don't miss this exciting preview story!
name: Prologue

description: The smash story from John Russo's Escape of the Living Dead series continues with art from super-star Mike (Friday the 13th) Wolfer! Before he was one of the undead, he was one of the living and now, the secrets of ESCAPE OF THE LIVING DEAD's breakout zombie star are revealed! Deadhead, the enigmatic, Stars and Stripes_x001E_wearing leader of the army of the walking dead is not like his rotting brethren. Something burns within him, something beyond the hunger for human flesh, something that the zombie multitude recognizes as a power that even they should fear. In the continuation of creator John Russo's saga of The Living Dead, the murder of the man that is Deadhead will be exposed as we witness the horrific events that now drive him in his inexhaustible pursuit of one thing... Make that two things: Human entrails and vengeance!

volume.name: Escape Of The Living Dead: Fearbook

description: Together for the the 1st time the acclaimed comic book series Final Death Race! Foreign intervention comes at a price but with rioting in the streets, natural resources running low and the economic horizon bleak America is forced to accept international entries to the Death Race. The president's only hope of regaining national pride is by Frankenstein Junior becoming king of the road!
name: TPB

description: Darkness spreads for the goddess of love. Venus struggles to pull her life together after the death of the man she treasures above all others, only to learn of a terrible scourge now growing deep inside her own body. Then, the call comes. Odyssey is mustered to confront evil happenings in the Underworld. Hitherto one of the group's most powerful members, Venus struggles to find her place. Some view her as more of a liability as she copes with looming mortality. Will she rise to the occasion, or put Odyssey at risk? Join Venus, 10th Muse, Atlas, Orion, and Judo Girl as they descend into a Hell within Hell. Join our heroes as they explore the true...Depths of Love.

Gunther Grizzwell is your average family bear, with a wife and kids, a day job, and a bottomless appetite for anything from roadkill to the occasional forest hiker. This e-book only collection of Grizzwells comics follows Gunther, his wife, Flora, and his kids, Tucker and Fauna, on their daily exploits both in and out of the home. We see Gunther's well-intentioned attempts at imparting fatherly wisdom, Tucker and Fauna's clever schemes for avoiding homework, and Flora's heroic efforts at preserving order amid her family's various misadventures.

Clever and sharply drawn, The Grizzwells is a funny and unpredictable spin on the traditional family comic strip--with bite. Created by award-winning artist Bill Schorr, it has been in syndication nationally for more than twenty years.

volume.name: The Grizzwells: I Can't Wait To Be A Dysfunctional Teenager

description:
For Gunther Grizzwell, holding down a day job is no simple feat. It takes dedication (to complete his daily naps), fortitude (to tolerate his irksome porcupine sidekick Pierpoint), and tenacity (to never stop searching for his next snack). In this e-book only collection of Grizzwells comics, Gunther and Pierpoint are the VIPs of the forest. Whether discussing the merits of daytime television, the latest confusing fashion trends, or their all-time favorite meals, every day at their woodland office is guaranteed to be comical, zany, and entirely unproductive.

Clever and sharply drawn, The Grizzwells is a funny and unpredictable spin on the traditional family comic strip--with bite. Created by award-winning artist Bill Schorr, it has been in syndication nationally for more than twenty years.

Nothing pleases Gunther Grizzwell like a good meal. Accompanied by his porcupine pal, the always-perplexing Pierpoint, Gunther roams the hills and campsites of the forest forever on the lookout for a tasty morsel of any shape or size. In this e-book only collection of Grizzwells comics, the duo ponders life's most important questions, such as: When it comes to road kill, is white or dark meat best? How important is presentation when serving up a delicious woodland creature? And which has the worst aftertaste, opossum omelets or stray Chihuahuas?

Clever and sharply drawn, The Grizzwells is a funny and unpredictable spin on the traditional family comic strip--with bite. Created by award-winning artist Bill Schorr, it has been in syndication nationally for more than twenty years.
After a typical happy day with his typical happy family, a young boy named Kevin wakes up to a world where everyone over the age of 18 wants to kill everyone UNDER the age of 18.

Angie, a British doctor, flew to Sicily for her best friend's wedding, where she meets her destined love. Bernardo was the half-brother of the groom, son of a great family in Sicily. She instantly fell in love with this na√Øve, thoughtful man, and spent wonderful moments just exchanging kisses. However, her love was quickly turned down the moment Bernardo found out Angie was from an upper-class family. "I was going to beg you to marry me. I've been living in a fool's paradise."
name: Vol. 1

description: After finding a man who had been attacked by a robber on the street, Meredith carries him into the hospital. But the man's younger brother, Rey, runs in half-cocked after hearing the news and, seeing Meredith dressed for a party, assumes she's a prostitute and accuses her of having had some part in the assault. Though random assaults involving criminals and prostitutes have been happening in the area recently, is that any way to treat your brother's savior? Frustrated and resentful, Meredith leaves the hospital room, but Rey appears at her house the next day, completely changed from the day before. Now meek and polite, he brings her an astonishing offer!
name: Vol. 1

description: Monsters Of The Silver Age presents Victor Vega, known to the world as Immortal Victor. In this tongue-in-cheek story, Victor is tracking an unknown villain, dubbed the Michelangelo Killer because victims are turned to stone. Victor suspects an ancient evil has returned, and joins forces with the Falconer, a local super hero who has unwittingly become very close to the real villain.

Rocket Robinson and the Pharaoh's Fortune is a classic adventure story for comic lovers of all ages! Follow 12-year-old adventurer Rocket Robinson and his friends Nuri and Screech as they navigate the dangers of 1930s Cairo in search of the greatest treasure in history--an ancient pharaoh's fortune hidden for centuries.
name: Vol. 1

volume.name: Rocket Robinson and the Pharaoh's Fortune

description: It's the Origin of Sir Roland! Learn how Sir Roland went from an empty suit of armor to the bravest knight in the realm! Also, how he met the Smart Ogre and the bonus origin of Sir Reginald, his Arch Nemesisifoos.

It's the year 2007, and Masaya's out in the woods with his friends when they bump into a mysterious boy(?) named Yuuki. His brains and brawn are both unparalleled, but he's pretty innocent in the ways of the world. Masaya's heart keeps beating faster whenever their paths cross... enjoy the sweeping, futuristic romance of Sleeping Next To You, but don't miss out on the other three exciting romances collected in this volume!
name: Vol. 1

description: The happiness of being together and the pain of being apart... He's the one who taught me everything... Jiro Kusunoki had always admired Yoshiyuki Kurihara from afar, drawn in by his slender frame and his big, beautiful eyes. Jiro joins the track and field team in order to get closer to his crush, but finds it difficult to keep up, as Kurihara always runs alone to isolate himself from others. Jiro perseveres, however, and the distance between them slowly starts to fade away... In addition to the main story, "Slow Starter," this masterpiece collection also includes three heartbreaking short stories.
name: Vol. 1

description:
Welcome to Betatown...where Sheriff is the only law enforcement droid; barely keeping the lid on a dilapidated ghetto of underused and under maintained industrial machines.

When he finds a naked, injured woman walking through Beta Town with no memory of how she got there, Sheriff is left with a serious problem. His programming states he must protect any human, but her pursuers are Alpha machines - his direct superiors. And they are prepared to risk a civil war to get her back...
name: Vol. 1

volume.name: Slumdroid: The Girl With The Hole In Her Head

description: Ariel has had an extraordinary life living all over the world, but at age 15, she wishes for nothing more than to have stability, friends, and the ability to do the ordinary things every girl her age would like to do. She has just moved reluctantly to the Twin Cities with her recently divorced mother Margie. As Margie tries to console Ariel after coming home from a gruelingly awkward first day at school, she suddenly collapsed without a reason. In a panic, Ariel seeks help from her neighbor Xigi, but she is quickly transported into another dimension. And a demon is after her...
name: Vol. 1

description:
Kids shouldn't talk to strangers, but they can't talk when their mouths are filled with candy! Snot, kids and candy in a special world of magic and bodily fluids, with a big runny-nosed blue bear as your guide. Part one of a three issue series. Diamond Previews Certified Cool.

Kevin Scalzo is a New York cartoonist, author and illustrator whose work has been shown in galleries and sold in bookstores around the world. He is known mainly for his color saturated paintings mixed with cartoon imagery. His comics have previously been published in Peter Bagge's Hate, B√™te Noire, the Top Shelf anthology and Suspect Device.
After his grandfather passes away, Chase Cassidy inherits a mysterious storage unit. Little does he know the secret inside will forever change his life.

Ten abandoned cats live in an old warehouse where they are looked after by a young girl named Annie. They include Chesney, the ringleader, Jack, his sidekick, and Oliver--a wide-eyed kitten. The warehouse contains a boardroom on the very top floor, where, unbeknownst to Annie the kitties conduct the world's business through the eyes of a cat.

In the e-book original Annie and the Cats, the cast is introduced with all their feline quirks.

In 2013, Ten Cats, created by Graham Harrop, won the National Cartoonist's Society Award for the Best Online Comics--Short Form division.

volume.name: Ten Cats: Annie and the Cats

description:
Ten abandoned cats live in an old warehouse where they are looked after by a young girl named Annie. They include Chesney, the ringleader, Jack, his sidekick, and Oliver--a wide-eyed kitten. The warehouse contains a boardroom on the very top floor, where, unbeknownst to Annie the kitties conduct the world's business through the eyes of a cat.

In the e-book original Chesney vs. Annie, Chesney continuously challenges Annie's cautious care-taking, but deep down cherishes being cared for.

In 2013, Ten Cats, created by Graham Harrop, won the National Cartoonist's Society Award for the Best Online Comics--Short Form division.

Ten abandoned cats live in an old warehouse where they are looked after by a young girl named Annie. They include Chesney, the ringleader, Jack, his sidekick, and Oliver--a wide-eyed kitten. The warehouse contains a boardroom on the very top floor, where, unbeknownst to Annie the kitties conduct the world's business through the eyes of a cat.

In the e-book original Ten Cats Enterprises, the cats hilariously take their turns at the board room table, making decisions about all things in their world, including how to make dogs do the lambada.

In 2013, Ten Cats, created by Graham Harrop, won the National Cartoonist's Society Award for the Best Online Comics--Short Form division.

Sometimes he's Thatababy Jones, venturing bravely into the Closet of Doom. Other times he's Superbaby, on a mission to improve any household object by outfitting it with a superhero's cape. Whatever world Thatababy inhabits, his imagination runs wild as he investigates important questions, such as: How many action figures does it take to clog a toilet? What are the hidden dangers of a prank call to the moon? And which makes a better imaginary friend: a tortoise, a raccoon, or the alien from Alien?

This e-book only collection of Thatababy's geekiest adventures features the crisp art and clever writing that earned the strip critical acclaim and a finalist's spot in Amazon's Comic Strip Superstars contest. It is the brainchild of Paul Trap, a freelance computer graphics illustrator and editorial cartoonist for Baseball America magazine.

Thatababy is always coloring outside the lines. And on the furniture. And the walls. And on himself. With a magic marker in his hand, the whole world is Thatababy's canvas. In this e-book only collection of cartoons from Paul Trap, Thatababy explores artistic pursuits ranging from creative at-home macaroni art (perfect for bejeweling Dad's ties), to the indoor uses for outdoor chalk (works on upholstery just as well as sidewalks), to the number of colors that can be made using only ingredients from the fridge. (Hint: All of them.)

Featuring the clean art and buoyant humor that earned the strip critical acclaim and a finalist's spot in Amazon's Comic Strip Superstars contest, Thatababy is the brainchild of Paul Trap, a freelance computer graphics illustrator and editorial cartoonist for Baseball America magazine.

When his parents are asleep and the gate to his crib is securely locked, that's when Thatababy really shines. His nightly solo concerts feature everything from country to classic rock, disco to doo-wop, and more often than not leave his mom and dad singing the blues. Thatababy is the infant born too busy to sleep, and through air guitar lessons, impromptu Van Halen dance parties, and other musical adventures with Mom and Dad, he's well on his way to becoming the world's most sonically sophisticated baby.

Thatababy Rocks Out is a funny and visually captivating e-book only collection of comic strips about life from the perspective of an infant with the uncanny ability to keep his parents on their toes. A finalist in Amazon's Comic Strip Superstars contest, it is the brainchild of Paul Trap, a freelance computer graphics illustrator and editorial cartoonist for Baseball America magazine.

The adventures of a mysterious ronin, a samurai assassin on the payroll of a powerful criminal organization, and his attempts to retain his soul and humanity as he faces off against the worst scum to be found on the streets of New York.
From Mast & Geoffo, after Pax Arena, meet The Walking Pandas!

Alan McLean, a wealthy businessman, is brutally murdered in his own home. It quickly becomes clear to Detectives Daniels and Harvey that things are not what they seem when a witness claims she saw the Grim Reaper at the murder scene.
name: Murder of A Fat Man

description:
Colonel Nick Fury, Director of the worldwide operating defense organisation SHIELD, discovers, that an evil mastermind funds some of the most dangerous super villains.

He assembles a secret ops team (with Spider-Man, Wolverine, Daredevil, Luke Cage and Captain America), to act against this threat. But one year later the past catches up with them ... and events take their course, which threaten the life of the team members and their friends and families.

Collects Secret War #1 - 5
name: Vol. 33 - Secret War

description: The book that inspired the film Blade Runner continues! Sci-fi author Philip K. Dick's award-winning Do Androids Dream Of Electric Sheep? has been called 'a masterpiece ahead of its time, even today' and served as the basis for Ridley Scott's film Blade Runner. BOOM! Studios presents the complete novel transplanted to the comic book medium, mixing all new panel-to-panel continuity with the actual text from the novel in an innovative, ground-breaking series experiment illustrated by acclaimed artist Tony Parker! Collects issues #9-12, including Jonathan Lethem's essay on being a Philip K. Dick fan.

description: Ivan the Terrible grew Moscow from a medieval nation state to an empire, but he had help. The machinations he used were terrible to behold, as he made a deal with Beelzebub. Kade has been working both sides of this nightmare, except instead of these two being at odds, they are in theory both allies, with each is trying to get the upper hand on the other. Beelzebub hasn't recognized Kade as the Demon Hunter, but when he begins to realize that Kade will rise to a higher level of power, he plots Kade's assassination.
